CommentBlocks.Comment:
This room data starts off as 16 bytes:
8 chaarcter numbers for the characters to use in the room - The high bit is ignored when drawing
8 attributes to use when drawing those characters
So a character could be listed twice with 2 different attributes

After the 16 bytes are various run lengths
If the byte value is 1 then the byte after it contains the number of character to clear (character value 0)
Otherwise the byte mean:
bits 0-2 : Character/Attribute index from above
bits 3-7 : Number of charatcters to draw using that character/attribute combination

The room data is terminated by a byte value of 0

IX points to start of room data which contains characters (0-7) and attributes (8-15)
HL points to run length data for room

Draw a horizontal line of characters to the screen
B contains number of chars

Convert character coords to screen address
BC contains cordinates
